Highest-priority comment:
The game currently allows multiple direction changes within a single movement interval (between MOVE_EVENT ticks). This lets players quickly press two keys (e.g., Up then Left while moving Right) and unintentionally perform an effective 180-degree turn within the same tick, causing an immediate self-collision. This is a common playability bug in Snake; standard behavior allows at most one direction change per move.

How to fix:
Throttle direction input to one accepted change per movement tick.

- In game.py, add a flag to track whether a direction change has been accepted in the current tick:
  - In Game.__init__: self._dir_changed = False
  - In Game.reset: self._dir_changed = False

- In Game.handle_input, guard direction changes with this flag and set it when a change is accepted:
  - Replace:
