        self.snake.set_direction(self.key_dir_map[event.key])
  - With:
    if event.key in self.key_dir_map and not self.game_over and not self._dir_changed:
        self.snake.set_direction(self.key_dir_map[event.key])
        self._dir_changed = True

- In Game.step, reset the flag at the start of each movement tick to allow one new change for the next interval:
  - At the very beginning of step() (after the game_over check), add:
    self._dir_changed = False

This ensures only one direction change is applied between moves, preventing unintended instantaneous reversals and self-collisions while preserving responsiveness.

